Title: 199. A Soldier's Story 2: Return from the Dead
description: In Watz Republic, Regina (Linda Ejiofor) confides in her friend, Zaya (Somkele Idhalama) to look after her younger brother while she goes after the desires of her heart to be with Major Egan (Tope Tedela).

Title: 200. Mandibles
description: When simple-minded friends Jean-Gab and Manu find a giant fly trapped in the boot of a car, they decide to train it in the hope of making a ton of cash.

Title: 201. Sputnik
description: The lone survivor of an enigmatic spaceship incident hasn't returned home alone - hiding inside his body is a dangerous creature.

Title: 202. Frank and Ava
description: Before he was chairman of the board. He was just a man, desperate for a woman, clinging to a dream. The story of Sinatra as never told before and Ava Gardner, the woman who saved him, by breaking him. Based on true stories.

Title: 203. The Rescue
description: A rescue unit within the Chinese Coast Guard are forced to overcome their personal differences to resolve a crisis.

Title: 204. Shithouse
description: A lonely college freshman forges a strong connection with his resident assistant during a fraternity party.

Title: 205. Never Rarely Sometimes Always
description: A pair of teenage girls in rural Pennsylvania travel to New York City to seek out medical help after an unintended pregnancy.

Title: 206. Centigrade
description: A married couple find themselves trapped in their frozen vehicle after a blizzard and struggle to survive amid plunging temperatures and unforeseen obstacles.

Title: 207. Equal Standard
description: The lives of New York City police officers collide with interwoven stories of race, rank, loss and betrayal.

Title: 208. Never Gonna Snow Again
description: Zhenia, a Russian-speaking immigrant from Ukraine, works as a masseur in Poland and becomes a guru-like figure in a wealthy gated community of his clients.

Title: 209. No Ordinary Man
description: No Ordinary Man is an in-depth look at the life of musician and trans culture icon Billy Tipton. Complicated, beautiful and historically unrivaled, this groundbreaking film shows what is possible when a community collaborates to honor the legacy of an unlikely hero.

Title: 210. Zappa
description: An in-depth look into the life and work of musician Frank Zappa.

Title: 211. American Deep State
description: For the first time, American people see the possibility that elected governments have to follow rules set by Washington D.C.'s bureaucratic institutions. From 1963 JFK's assassination to 2016 Russia Collusion Conspiracy.

Title: 212. Cicada
description: A New York love story that toes the line between narrative and doc with two actors reliving parts of their own experiences.

Title: 213. Stray
description: The world of Zeytin, a stray dog living life on the streets of Istanbul.

Title: 214. The Meaning of Hitler
description: An inquiry into decades of cultural fascination with the Nazi leader, and the ramifications of such a fascination on present day politics.

Title: 215. Lorelei
description: Waylon is released from prison after 15 years. He reunited with Dolores, his high school girlfriend, who is now a single mother of three follows is a lyrical take on love regret and second chances.

Title: 216. Adverse
description: A rideshare driver discovers that his sister is in debt to a dangerous crime syndicate.

Title: 217. Sweat
description: Three days in the life of fitness motivator Sylwia Zajac, a social media celebrity surrounded by loyal employees and admirers, who is really looking for true intimacy.

Title: 218. Twiceborn
description: Follows Satoru, a successful businessman who relinquishes everything to pursue his true calling: the happiness of humankind.

Title: 219. Minyan
description: A young Jewish man is caught between thrilling private trysts and his repressive family in this thoughtful drama set in 1980s Brooklyn.

Title: 220. Powerbomb
description: Powerbomb is the story of an independent wrestler on the verge of breaking into the big time, but he's contemplating leaving it all behind to spend more time with his family. When our wrestler's biggest fan hears the news, he decides to take matters into his own hands to ensure that his champion gets to the top by any means necessary.

Title: 221. About Hope
description: Thomas McKenzie has been searching for the perfect girl his whole life. When he meets two women who pique his interest, he learns that the love we are searching for is not always the true love that makes us whole.

Title: 222. Little Girl
description: The touching portrait of eight-year-old Sasha, who questions her gender and in doing so, evokes the sometimes disturbing reactions of a society that is still invested in a biological boy-girl way of thinking.

Title: 223. Coded Bias
description: When MIT Media Lab researcher Joy Buolamwini discovers that facial recognition does not see dark-skinned faces accurately, she embarks on a journey to push for the first-ever U.S. legislation against bias in algorithms that impact us all.

Title: 224. Can You Bring It: Bill T. Jones and D-Man in the Waters
description: Can You Bring It: Bill T. Jones and D-Man in the Waters is a feature documentary that traces the history and legacy of one of the most important works of art to come out of the age of AIDS - Bill T. Jones' tour de force ballet "D-Man in the Waters". In 1989, "D-Man in the Waters" gave physical manifestation to the fear, anger, grief, and hope for salvation that the Bill T. Jones/Arnie Zane Company felt as they were embattled by the AIDS pandemic. As a group of young dancers reconstructs the dance, they learn about this oft forgotten history and deepen their understanding of the power of art in a time of plague. Bill T. Jones is arguably the most socially, politically and emotionally compelling choreographer alive today. Thirty years ago, he embedded motifs of risk and sacrifice, love, loss and resurrection in the choreography for "D-Man in the Waters". Through an extraordinary series of interviews, archival material, and uniquely powerful cinematography of movement, this 90-minute, lyrical documentary uses the story of this dance to illustrate the triumph of the human spirit in art and in the community. Today, by learning the dance, a new generation reinvigorates the spirit of a community fighting to survive.

Title: 225. Stardust
description: Chronicles the young David Bowie's first visit to the US in 1971 - a trip that inspired the invention of his iconic alter ego Ziggy Stardust.

Title: 226. Kindred
description: Plagued by mysterious hallucinations, a pregnant woman suspects that the family of her deceased boyfriend has intentions for her unborn child.

Title: 227. Enemies of the State
description: An American family becomes entangled in a bizarre web of secrets and lies when their hacker son is targeted by the U.S. government, making them all ENEMIES OF THE STATE.

Title: 228. The Trip to Greece
description: Actors Rob Brydon and Steve Coogan travel from Troy to Ithaca following in the footsteps of the Odysseus.

Title: 229. There Is No Evil
description: The four stories that are variations on the crucial themes of moral strength and the death penalty that ask to what extent individual freedom can be expressed under a despotic regime and its seemingly inescapable threats.

Title: 230. Resistance
description: The story of mime Marcel Marceau as he works with a group of Jewish boy scouts and the French Resistance to save the lives of ten thousand orphans during World War II.

Title: 231. Gossamer Folds
description: Uprooted to a Kansas City neighborhood, a 10-year-old boy develops an unlikely friendship with a retired professor and his transgender daughter.

Title: 232. I Am Lisa
description: A sadistic, small-town sheriff and her underlings brutalize Lisa and leave her for dead in the woods. Bitten by a werewolf and bestowed with supernatural abilities, can Lisa retain her humanity as she exacts revenge?

Title: 233. What We Found
description: A trio of friends are starting high school when their friend vanishes. With the police unable--or unwilling?--to find her, they take it upon themselves to find out what happened, undertaking a harrowing journey that will change them all.

Title: 234. 12 Hour Shift
description: Bodies start to pile up when a drug-user nurse and her cousin try to find a replacement kidney for an organ trafficker.

Title: 235. Bang! Bang!
description: When five teenagers decide to rob a supermarket, they quickly discover that their actions have consequences.

Title: 236. Blood Widow
description: A serial killer is terrorizing Arizona with the police in hot pursuit. What the police don't know is that a mysterious group are also pursuing the same killer to stop the killer from unleashing an evil like nothing before.

Title: 237. Unoponchash Batash
description: A university student falls in love with a medical sales representative. Things spiral out of control after tragedy strikes, and the student becomes obsessed.

Title: 238. Sex and the Future
description: Two socially inept inventors create a female robot and realize they can profit from mass production. A wealthy prince discovers their invention, leading to a bizarre plan involving world domination and redefining gender norms.

Title: 239. Memories of My Father
description: An author recalls life with his father, a university professor who fought against oppression and social inequality in Colombia in the seventies.

Title: 240. Still Here
description: A New York journalist who gets assigned the story of a missing African-American young girl, risks his career and takes the matter into his own hands trying to find her.

Title: 241. Breaking Bread
description: Dr. Nof Atamna-Ismaeel - the first Muslim Arab to win Israel's MasterChef - is on a quest to make social change through food. And so, she founded the A-sham Arabic Food Festival, where pairs of Arab and Jewish chefs collaborate on exotic dishes like kishek (a Syrian yogurt soup), and qatayef (a dessert typically served during Ramadan). A film about hope, synergy and mouthwatering fare, Breaking Bread illustrates what happens when people focus on the person, rather than her religion; on the public, rather than the politicians.

Title: 242. Ottolenghi and the Cakes of Versailles
description: Follows chef Yotam on his quest to bring the sumptuous art and decadence of Versailles to life in cake form at the Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York.

Title: 243. Farewell Amor
description: Reunited after 17 years, an Angolan immigrant is joined in the U.S. by his wife and daughter. Now strangers sharing a one-bedroom apartment, they discover a shared love of dance that may help them overcome the distance between them.

Title: 244. No Place
description: Mac travels the country looking for the next hustle. After he wraps up business with his Midwest fixer Les, she turns him on to a big score in Indianapolis with a local bar owner. He finds out it involves his old flame Evelyn and soon discovers that his past has caught up with him and he may not make it out alive.

Title: 245. Dear Santa
description: 'Dear Santa' shines a light on the 100-year-old 'Operation Santa' Program of the United States Postal Service. Each year, hundreds of thousands of letters to Santa arrive at Post Offices around the country. Through Operation Santa, the United States Postal Service makes it possible for the public to safely adopt these letters and make children's dreams come true. The film invites audiences along for the magic of this massive endeavor. Traveling the country, much like Santa does on Christmas Eve, the film focuses on select 'Operation Santa' Centers: some in metropolitan areas like the massive operation in New York City and others in small towns where the Post Office is the heart of the community.

Title: 246. King's Gambit
description: King's Gambit is an Independent, live-action feature film set in present-day Florida about Bryce, a man who uses a mystic journal to alter the world around him.

Title: 247. Bump Kowalski and the Ten Commandments
description: Bump Kowalski is a washed up pinball wizard on the path to repair his pinball past.

Title: 248. Love It Was Not
description: The tragic love story of Helena Citron, a young Jewish prisoner in Auschwitz, and Austrian SS officer Franz Wunsch.

Title: 249. Simple Passion
description: A mother falls into an addictive relationship with a Russian diplomat, with whom she has nothing in common.

Title: 250. The Roads Not Taken
description: A day in the life of Leo and his daughter, Molly, as he floats through alternate lives he could have lived, leading Molly to wrestle with her own path as she considers her future.

Title: 251. Paper Spiders
description: A bittersweet story about coming of age in the shadow of mental illness.

Title: 252. Slalom
description: Under the guidance of a strict ex champion, a promising 15 year old girl trains as a professional skiing star.Will she be able to endure the physical and emotional pressures?

Title: 253. Crock of Gold: A Few Rounds with Shane MacGowan
description: A look at the life of Irish singer/songwriter and Pogues frontman Shane MacGowan.

Title: 254. Moondance
description: A rogue director turns a run-of-the-mill Hollywood love story into a big band musical with the help of his crew and the out-of-the-loop actors.

Title: 255. 10 Days with Dad
description: Antoine is the Head of HR of a big company. When his wife decides to go on holiday and leave him with the responsibility of their four kids, he knows it will be easy. But Antoine has underestimated the mess that it can be.

Title: 256. Mermaid in Paris
description: A man rescues a mermaid in Paris and slowly falls in love with her.

Title: 257. The Bay of Silence
description: Will believes his wife Rosalind is innocent of their son's suspected murder, only to discover the devastating truth behind her past links her to another unsolved crime.

Title: 258. Night Shift
description: Three officers are tasked with escorting an illegal immigrant to Charles de Gaulle airport, where he will be forced onto a plane and sent back to his homeland. But when they find out about the truth, they have to make a difficult choice.

Title: 259. The Fox Hunter
description: A prominent Southern family of blue-blood media moguls deteriorates at the crossroads of past and progress in matters of death, wealth, love and American journalism.

Title: 260. Fear Pharm
description: Four people enter a corn maze for Halloween and are picked off one by one by the twisted family who own the scare attraction.

Title: 261. Hai Tang Hong
description: "Hai Tang Hong" tells a tragic story of opera artist Haitanghong. It profoundly exposes the oppression and bullying of the opera artists by the evil forces in the old times, praises the great love of the world and embodies the traditional virtues of the Chinese nation.

Title: 262. Parallel Policy
description: This film delivers a conscientious perspective of the major policy changes made by President Donald Trump, former EPA Administrator Scott Pruitt and DOE Secretary Rick Perry to the American stance on climate change, carbon emissions and environmental destruction.

Title: 263. The Evil Next Door
description: A dad moves into a new house with his son and girlfriend. When he's out of town working, the son makes a new "friend" next door.

Title: 264. I Need You Dead!
description: After a moment of total teenage angst, a young punk finds himself at odds with a psychedelic monster of his own creation.

Title: 265. Sol
description: Sol, a famous Argentine Tango performer, has lived in Buenos Aires for many years. Behind her excessive temper and her glowing smile, the Diva hides an injury from which she never really recovered: the loss of her only son, Raphaël.

Title: 266. Granny Nanny
description: Three frustrated pensioners volunteer themselves as Grand-Godparents to three stressed children.

Title: 267. It's for Your Own Good
description: Three fathers who are also brothers-in-law make a pact to save their daughters from their boyfriends.

Title: 268. The East
description: A young Dutch soldier deployed to suppress post-WWII independence efforts in the Netherlands' colony of Indonesia finds himself torn between duty and conscience when he joins an increasingly ruthless commander's elite squad.

Title: 269. 365 Days
description: Massimo is a member of the Sicilian Mafia family and Laura is a sales director. She does not expect that on a trip to Sicily trying to save her relationship, Massimo will kidnap her and give her 365 days to fall in love with him.

Title: 270. You Should Have Left
description: A former banker, his actress wife, and their spirited daughter book a vacation at an isolated modern home in the Welsh countryside where nothing is quite as it seems.

Title: 271. Hamilton
description: The real life of one of America's foremost founding fathers and first Secretary of the Treasury, Alexander Hamilton. Captured live on Broadway from the Richard Rodgers Theater with the original Broadway cast.

Title: 272. Enola Holmes
description: When Enola Holmes, Sherlock's sister, discovers her mother is missing, she endeavors to find her, becoming a super-sleuth in her own right as she outwits her famous brother and unravels a dangerous conspiracy.

Title: 273. The Devil All the Time
description: Sinister characters converge around a young man devoted to protecting those he loves in a postwar backwoods town teeming with corruption and brutality

Title: 274. Greenland
description: A family struggles for survival in the face of a cataclysmic natural disaster.

Title: 275. Hillbilly Elegy
description: An urgent phone call pulls a Yale Law student back to his Ohio hometown, where he reflects on three generations of family history and his own future.

Title: 276. Mulan
description: To keep her ailing father from serving in the Imperial Army, a fearless young woman disguises herself as a man and battles northern invaders in China.

Title: 277. Boss Level
description: Trapped in a time loop that constantly repeats the day of his murder, a former special forces agent must unlock the mystery behind his untimely demise.

Title: 278. Another Round
description: Four high-school teachers consume alcohol on a daily basis to see how it affects their social and professional lives.

Title: 279. Run
description: Chloe, a teenager who is confined to a wheelchair, is homeschooled by her mother, Diane. Chloe soon becomes suspicious of her mother and begins to suspect that she may be harboring a dark secret.

Title: 280. Greyhound
description: Several months after the U.S. entry into World War II, an inexperienced U.S. Navy commander must lead an Allied convoy being stalked by a German submarine wolf pack.

Title: 281. The Old Guard
description: A covert group of tight-knit mercenaries with an inability to die have fought to protect the world for centuries. But when their abilities are suddenly exposed, they need to eliminate the threat of those who seek to replicate their power.

Title: 282. The Banker
description: In the 1960s, two African-American entrepreneurs hire a working-class white man to pretend to be the head of their business empire while they pose as a janitor and chauffeur.

Title: 283. I Care a Lot
description: A crooked legal guardian who drains the savings of her elderly wards meets her match when a woman she tries to swindle turns out to be more than she first appears.

Title: 284. Extraction
description: Tyler Rake, a fearless black market mercenary, embarks on the most deadly extraction of his career when he's enlisted to rescue the kidnapped son of an imprisoned international crime lord.

Title: 285. Dinner in America
description: An on-the-lam punk rocker and a young woman obsessed with his band unexpectedly fall in love and go on an epic journey together through America's decaying Midwestern suburbs.

Title: 286. I'm Thinking of Ending Things
description: Full of misgivings, a young woman travels with her new boyfriend to his parents' secluded farm. Upon arriving, she comes to question everything she thought she knew about him, and herself.

Title: 287. We Can Be Heroes
description: When alien invaders capture the Earth's superheroes, their kids must learn to work together to save their parents and the planet.

Title: 288. Life in a Year
description: The movie follows 17-year-old Daryn who finds out that his girlfriend is dying. He sets out to give her an entire life in the last year she has left.

Title: 289. Inheritance
description: The patriarch of a wealthy and powerful family suddenly passes away, leaving his daughter with a shocking secret inheritance that threatens to unravel and destroy the family.

Title: 290. Eurovision Song Contest: The Story of Fire Saga
description: When aspiring musicians Lars and Sigrit are given the opportunity to represent their country at the world's biggest song competition, they finally have a chance to prove that any dream worth having is a dream worth fighting for.

Title: 291. Mank
description: 1930s Hollywood is re-evaluated through the eyes of scathing social critic and alcoholic screenwriter Herman J. Mankiewicz as he races to finish the screenplay of Citizen Kane (1941).

Title: 292. All the Bright Places
description: The story of Violet and Theodore, who meet and change each other's lives forever. As they struggle with the emotional and physical scars of their past, they discover that even the smallest places and moments can mean something.

Title: 293. Lost Girls and Love Hotels
description: Disillusioned with the world she knows, a woman searches for meaning and affirmations of life with a dashing Yakuza gangster in Tokyo.

Title: 294. Spenser Confidential
description: When two Boston police officers are murdered, ex-cop Spenser teams up with his no-nonsense roommate Hawk to take down criminals.

Title: 295. The Trial of the Chicago 7
description: The story of 7 people on trial stemming from various charges surrounding the uprising at the 1968 Democratic National Convention in Chicago, Illinois.

Title: 296. An American Pickle
description: An immigrant worker at a pickle factory is accidentally preserved for 100 years and wakes up in modern-day Brooklyn.

Title: 297. The Night Clerk
description: A voyeuristic hotel clerk becomes the subject of a murder investigation.

Title: 298. Rebecca
description: A young newlywed arrives at her husband's imposing family estate on a windswept English coast and finds herself battling the shadow of his first wife, Rebecca, whose legacy lives on in the house long after her death.

Title: 299. Project Power
description: When a pill that gives its users unpredictable superpowers for five minutes hits the streets of New Orleans, a teenage dealer and a local cop must team with an ex-soldier to take down the group responsible for its creation.

Title: 300. Wolfwalkers
description: A young apprentice hunter and her father journey to Ireland to help wipe out the last wolf pack. But everything changes when she befriends a free-spirited girl from a mysterious tribe rumored to transform into wolves by night.

Title: 301. Run Hide Fight
description: Zoe Hull, 17, uses her wits, survival skills, and compassion to fight for her life, and the lives of her classmates, against a group of live-streaming school shooters.

Title: 302. Body Cam
description: When a routine traffic stop results in the unexplained, grisly death of her colleague, a cop realizes footage of the incident will play for her eyes only. As the attacks mount, she races to understand the supernatural force behind them.

Title: 303. Cuties
description: Eleven-year-old Amy starts to rebel against her conservative family's traditions when she becomes fascinated with a free-spirited dance crew.

Title: 304. The Call
description: Two people live in different times. Seo-Yeon lives in the present and Young-Sook lives in the past. One phone call connects the two, and their lives are changed irrevocably.

Title: 305. Borat Subsequent Moviefilm
description: Borat returns to America from Kazakhstan to America, this time to reveal more about the American culture, the COVID-19 pandemic, and the political elections.

Title: 306. The Babysitter: Killer Queen
description: Two years after Cole survived a satanic blood cult, he's living another nightmare: high school. And the demons from his past? Still making his life hell.

Title: 307. The Wrong Missy
description: Tim thinks he's invited the woman of his dreams on a work retreat to Hawaii, realizing too late he mistakenly texted someone from a nightmare blind date.

Title: 308. Pieces of a Woman
description: When a young mother's home birth ends in unfathomable tragedy, she begins a year-long odyssey of mourning that fractures relationships with loved ones in this deeply personal story of a woman learning to live alongside her loss.

Title: 309. Escape from Pretoria
description: Based on the real-life prison break of two political captives, Escape From Pretoria is a race-against-time thriller set in the tumultuous apartheid days of South Africa.

Title: 310. Spontaneous
description: Get ready for the outrageous coming-of-age love story about growing up...and blowing up. When students in their school begin exploding (literally), seniors Mara and Dylan struggle to survive in a world where each moment may be their last.

Title: 311. The Midnight Sky
description: This post-apocalyptic tale follows Augustine, a lonely scientist in the Arctic, as he races to stop Sully and her fellow astronauts from returning home to a mysterious global catastrophe.

Title: 312. Host
description: Six friends hire a medium to hold a seance via Zoom during lockdown, but they get far more than they bargained for as things quickly go wrong.

Title: 313. Lucy Shimmers and the Prince of Peace
description: Second chances start when a hardened criminal crosses paths with a precocious little girl who is helped by an angel to change hearts during the holiday season.

Title: 314. Force of Nature
description: A gang of thieves plan a heist during a hurricane and encounter trouble when a cop tries to force everyone in the building to evacuate.

Title: 315. Hubie Halloween
description: Despite his devotion to his hometown of Salem (and its Halloween celebration), Hubie Dubois is a figure of mockery for kids and adults alike. But this year, something is going bump in the night, and it's up to Hubie to save Halloween.

Title: 316. The One and Only Ivan
description: A gorilla named Ivan tries to piece together his past with the help of an elephant named Ruby as they hatch a plan to escape from captivity.

Title: 317. The King of Staten Island
description: Scott has been a case of arrested development since his firefighter dad died. He spends his days smoking weed and dreaming of being a tattoo artist until events force him to grapple with his grief and take his first steps forward in life.

Title: 318. Superdeep
description: A small research team went down below the surface to find out what secret the world's deepest borehole was hiding. What they have found turned out to be the greatest threat in history. And the future of humanity is in their hands.

Title: 319. The High Note
description: A superstar singer and her overworked personal assistant are presented with a choice that could alter the course of their respective careers.

Title: 320. Capone
description: After a 10 year stint, former bootlegger and notorious criminal Al Capone starts to show signs of dementia, forcing him to face the demons of his violent past.

Title: 321. The Craft: Legacy
description: A group of high school students form a coven of witches.

Title: 322. The Comeback Trail
description: A film producer who owes money to a mobster tries to "accidentally" kill his aging movie star for an insurance scam so he can payoff his debt, but he begins to realize that the movie they're shooting is a masterpiece in the making.

Title: 323. Caveat
description: A lone drifter suffering from partial memory loss accepts a job to look after a psychologically troubled woman in an abandoned house on an isolated island.

Title: 324. The Forgotten Battle
description: In WWII's final years, a soldier in the German army, a British glider pilot, and a Dutch resistance fighter's paths intertwine. Their choices shape destinies, impacting not only their freedom but also that of others.

Title: 325. A Fall from Grace
description: Disheartened since her ex-husband's affair, Grace Waters feels restored by a new romance. But when secrets erode her short-lived joy, Grace's vulnerable side turns violent.

Title: 326. Skylines
description: When a virus threatens to turn the now earth-dwelling friendly alien hybrids against humans, Captain Rose Corley must lead a team of elite mercenaries on a mission to the alien world in order to save what's left of humanity.

Title: 327. Sergio
description: A sweeping drama set in the chaotic aftermath of the US invasion of Iraq, where the life of top UN diplomat Sergio Vieira de Mello hangs in the balance during the most treacherous mission of his career.

Title: 328. My Octopus Teacher
description: A filmmaker forges an unusual friendship with an octopus living in a South African kelp forest, learning as the animal shares the mysteries of her world.

Title: 329. Alone
description: When an outbreak hits, Aidan barricades himself inside his apartment and starts rationing food. His complex is overrun by infected Screamers, and with the world falling apart into chaos, he is left completely alone fighting for his life.

Title: 330. The Social Dilemma
description: Explores the dangerous human impact of social networking; tech experts sound the alarm on their own creations.

Title: 331. On the Rocks
description: A young mother reconnects with her larger-than-life playboy father on an adventure through New York.

Title: 332. The Secret Garden
description: An orphaned girl discovers a magical garden hidden at her strict uncle's estate.

Title: 333. The Things We Say, the Things We Do
description: Waiting for her boyfriend to join her on a country vacation, three months pregnant Daphne bonds with his cousin Maxime, and their shared intimacy brings them closer together into a full fledged love affair.

Title: 334. Artemis Fowl
description: Artemis Fowl, a young criminal prodigy, hunts down a secret society of fairies to find his missing father.

Title: 335. Horse Girl
description: Sarah, a socially isolated woman with a fondness for arts and crafts, horses, and supernatural crime shows finds her increasingly lucid dreams trickling into her waking life.

Title: 336. Songbird
description: In 2024 a pandemic ravages the world and its cities. Centering on a handful of people as they navigate the obstacles currently hindering society: disease, martial law, quarantine, and vigilantes.

Title: 337. Misbehaviour
description: A group of women hatch a plan to disrupt the 1970 Miss World beauty competition in London.

Title: 338. The Secret: Dare to Dream
description: A feature film adaptation of the self-help book, 'The Secret', which focuses on the power of positive thinking.

Title: 339. Nocturne
description: An incredibly gifted pianist makes a Faustian bargain to overtake her twin sister at a prestigious institution for classical musicians.

Title: 340. His House
description: A refugee couple makes a harrowing escape from war-torn South Sudan, but then they struggle to adjust to their new life in an English town that has an evil lurking beneath the surface.

Title: 341. The Prom
description: A troupe of hilariously self-obsessed theater stars swarm into a small conservative Indiana town in support of a high-school girl who wants to take her girlfriend to the prom.

Title: 342. Work It
description: When Quinn Ackerman's admission to the college of her dreams depends on her performance at a dance competition, she forms a ragtag group of dancers to take on the best squad in school. Now she just needs to learn how to dance.

Title: 343. The Kissing Booth 2
description: In the sequel to 2018's The Kissing Booth', high school senior Elle juggles a long-distance relationship with her dreamy boyfriend Noah, college applications, and a new friendship with a handsome classmate that could change everything.

Title: 344. The Doorman
description: A woman returns from combat and befriends a family in NYC. A gang of thieves plot to take the family's valuables, and she is all that stands between them and their lives.

Title: 345. The Half of It
description: When smart but cash-strapped teen Ellie Chu agrees to write a love letter for a jock, she doesn't expect to become his friend - or fall for his crush.

Title: 346. Lost Girls
description: After Mari Gilbert's daughter disappears, police inaction drives her own investigation into the gated Long Island community where Shannan was last seen. Her search brings attention to over a dozen murdered sex workers.

Title: 347. Mortal
description: Fantasy adventure origin story about a young man discovering he has god-like powers based on ancient Norse mythology.

Title: 348. My Spy
description: A hardened CIA operative finds himself at the mercy of a precocious 9-year-old girl, having been sent undercover to surveil her family.

Title: 349. Clouds
description: Based on real events, a young musician discovers his cancer has spread, leaving him just a few months to live. With limited time, he follows his dream and makes an album, unaware that it will soon be a viral music phenomenon.

Title: 350. My First Summer
description: Isolated Claudia hides away on a remote property after her mother's death. Shocked when spirited local teen Grace appears in her garden, the pair find support and love in each other.

Title: 351. Worth
description: An attorney in Washington D.C. battles against cynicism, bureaucracy and politics to help the victims of 9/11.

Title: 352. Ghosts of War
description: Five American soldiers assigned to hold a French Chateau near the end of World War II. This unexpected respite quickly descends into madness when they encounter a supernatural enemy more terrifying than anything seen on the battlefield.

Title: 353. Divine
description: Tells the story of insecure Gregory Spring, who first has to fly to Vatican City in order to overcome his fears, report on the election of the pope and to fall in love.

Title: 354. A Nice Girl Like You
description: After being accused of being too inhibited by her ex-boyfriend, a violinist creates a rather wild to-do list that sends her on a whirlwind journey of self-discovery.

Title: 355. Chemical Hearts
description: A teenage boy falls in love with a troubled girl who transfers to his high school.

Title: 356. American Murder: The Family Next Door
description: In 2018, 34-year-old Shanann Watts and her two young daughters disappear in Colorado. With the heartbreaking details emerging, the family's story made headlines around the world.

Title: 357. Books of Blood
description: A journey into uncharted and forbidden territory through three tales tangled in space and time.

Title: 358. Palm Swings
description: After moving to Palm Springs, a young married couple puts their love to the test when they discover their neighbors are swingers.

Title: 359. The Sleepover
description: When two siblings discover their seemingly normal mom is a former thief in witness protection who has been forced to pull one last job, they team up to rescue her over the course of an action-packed night.

Title: 360. Charm City Kings
description: Fourteen-year-old Mouse desperately wants to join the Midnight Clique, an infamous group of Baltimore dirt-bike riders who rule the summertime streets.

Title: 361. Skin: A History of Nudity in the Movies
description: The story chronicles nudity's evolution in cinema from silent era through #MeToo, examining moral shifts, gender dynamics, artistic intent vs. exploitation, and nudity's role in storytelling amid proliferation of compelling content.

Title: 362. The Last Champion
description: When his mother dies, scandal-ridden ex-Olympian John Wright returns to a hometown that has not forgiven him.

Title: 363. Feel the Beat
description: After failing to find success on Broadway, April returns to her hometown and reluctantly is recruited to train a misfit group of young dancers for a big competition.

Title: 364. Holidate
description: Fed up with being single on holidays, two strangers agree to be each other's platonic plus-ones all year long, only to catch real feelings along the way.

Title: 365. Dangerous Lies
description: When a wealthy elderly man dies and unexpectedly leaves his estate to his new caregiver, she's drawn into a web of deception and murder. If she's going to survive, she'll have to question everyone's motives - even the people she loves.

Title: 366. Unpregnant
description: A 17-year old Missouri teen named Veronica discovers she has gotten pregnant, a development that threatens to end her dreams of matriculating at an Ivy League college, and the career that will follow.

Title: 367. Happiest Season
description: A holiday romantic comedy that captures the range of emotions tied to wanting your family's acceptance, being true to yourself, and trying not to ruin Christmas.

Title: 368. Da 5 Bloods
description: Four black veterans battle the forces of man and nature when they return to Vietnam seeking the remains of their fallen squad leader and the gold fortune he helped them hide.

Title: 369. Over the Moon
description: In this animated musical, a girl builds a rocket ship and blasts off, hoping to meet a mythical moon goddess.

Title: 370. Antebellum
description: Successful author Veronica Henley finds herself trapped in a horrifying reality and must uncover the mind-bending mystery before it's too late.

Title: 371. Let Them All Talk
description: A famous author goes on a cruise trip with her friends and nephew in an effort to find fun and happiness while she comes to terms with her troubled past.

Title: 372. Kalashnikov
description: Wounded as a tank driver in 1941 during World War II, Mikhail Timofeyevich Kalashnikov sees the latest Soviet machine gun fail. As he's also an inventor, he starts making improvements and in 1947 ends up creating the AK-47 assault rifle.

Title: 373. Sunrise in Heaven
description: A true love story that spans a lifetime but eventually results in a painful loss of love. Jan is the daughter of an overly protective military father, but that doesn't stop her from falling love with Steve, a young GI in the Air Force.

Title: 374. #Alive
description: The rapid spread of an unknown infection has left an entire city in ungovernable chaos, but one survivor remains alive in isolation. It is his story.

Title: 375. Uncle Frank
description: In 1973, when Frank Bledsoe and his 18-year-old niece Beth take a road trip from Manhattan to Creekville, South Carolina, for the family patriarch's funeral, they're unexpectedly joined by Frank's lover, Walid.

Title: 376. Villain
description: Eddie Franks is a former criminal who attempts to help his family by reconnecting with his daughter and clearing his brother's debt. Despite his efforts, he is drawn back into a criminal way of life, with devastating consequences.

Title: 377. Arkansas
description: Kyle and Swin live by the orders of an Arkansas-based drug kingpin named Frog, whom they've never met. But when a deal goes horribly wrong, the consequences are deadly.

Title: 378. Jiu Jitsu
description: Every six years, an ancient order of jiu-jitsu fighters joins forces to battle a vicious race of alien invaders. But when a celebrated war hero goes down in defeat, the fate of the planet and mankind hangs in the balance.

Title: 379. Butchers
description: A family of sadistic butchers has dug into the back country and, from the deep freeze of winter to the dog days of summer, anyone who crosses their path is dead meat.

Title: 380. Grizzly II: Revenge
description: All hell breaks loose when a giant Grizzly, reacting to the slaughter of Grizzlies by poachers, attacks at a massive big-band rock concert in the National Park.

Title: 381. The Occupant
description: Javier Muñoz, once a successful executive, makes the fateful decision to leave his home, which he and his family can no longer afford.

Title: 382. The Very Excellent Mr. Dundee
description: Paul Hogan is reluctantly thrust back into the spotlight as he desperately attempts to restore his sullied reputation on the eve of being knighted.

Title: 383. Big Boys Don't Cry
description: Connolly recalls childhood in children's home after police probe friend's suicide. He struggles to connect with Anthea while confronting those behind his troubled past and friend's death. Inspired by real events.

Title: 384. The Postcard Killings
description: A New York detective investigates the death of his daughter who was murdered while on her honeymoon in London.

Title: 385. Proximity
description: A young NASA JPL scientist is abducted by extraterrestrials, but when no one believes his story he becomes obsessed with finding proof, which leads him on a journey of discovery.

Title: 386. Guest House
description: An newly engaged couple's buys their dream house but it comes with one small catch, a perennial party animal who lives in the guesthouse.

Title: 387. Valley Girl
description: A pair of young lovers from different backgrounds defy their parents and friends to stay together, set to a New Wave '80s soundtrack. A musical adaptation of the 1983 film.

Title: 388. Last Moment of Clarity
description: Three years after witnessing the murder of his fiancée, a man finds himself a fearful drifter, until one day at a Parisian cinema he sees an actress who looks a lot like his dead love, and eventually he finds the truth about his fiancée.

Title: 389. To All the Boys: P.S. I Still Love You
description: Lara Jean and Peter have just taken their relationship from pretend to officially official when another recipient of one of her old love letters enters the picture.

Title: 390. Ma Rainey's Black Bottom
description: Tensions rise when trailblazing blues singer Ma Rainey and her band gather at a recording studio in Chicago in 1927.

Title: 391. Boys from County Hell
description: A crew of hardy road workers, led by a bickering father and son, must survive the night when they accidentally awaken an ancient Irish vampire.

Title: 392. Irresistible
description: A Democratic strategist helps a retired veteran run for mayor in a small, conservative Midwest town.

Title: 393. The Glorias
description: The story of feminist icon Gloria Steinem's itinerant childhood and its influence on her life as a writer, activist and organizer for women's rights worldwide.

Title: 394. Big Freaking Rat
description: Ranger BRODY, with the help of his nephew and niece DYLAN and NAOMI, is preparing to open the brand-new campground for the season. Everything is in order and the camp seems peaceful until a GIANT RAT, mutated from multiple dumping of toxic wastes, begins killing the campers and rangers.

Title: 395. Black Bear
description: A filmmaker at a creative impasse seeks solace from her tumultuous past at a rural retreat, only to find that the woods summon her inner demons in intense and surprising ways.
One man's journey to the future to save a dying world.

Title: 397. Josee, the Tiger and the Fish
description: After befriending a marine biology student, a sarcastic artist living with paraplegia begins to experience the world beyond her home.

Title: 398. The Windermere Children
description: This is the stark, moving, and ultimately redemptive story of the bonds these children make with one another, and of how the friendships forged at Windermere become a lifeline to a fruitful future.

Title: 399. Flashback
description: After a chance encounter with a man forgotten from his youth, Fred literally and metaphorically journeys into his past.

Title: 400. The Paramedic
description: Angel works in an ambulance service. After a tragic accident, his personal life begins to deteriorate as he becomes more and more suspicious of his partner Vane.

Title: 401. Black Beauty
description: A wild horse and a teenage girl forge an unbreakable bond which keeps them connected for a lifetime.

Title: 402. Looks That Kill
description: The story of a teenage boy who deals with the ups and downs of being lethally attractive.

Title: 403. Black Box
description: After losing his wife and his memory in a car accident, a single father undergoes an agonizing experimental treatment that causes him to question who he really is.

Title: 404. The Last Thing He Wanted
description: A veteran D.C. journalist loses the thread of her own narrative when a guilt-propelled errand for her father thrusts her from byline to unwitting subject in the very story she's trying to break. Adapted from Joan Didion's namesake novel.

Title: 405. Monsters of Man
description: A US weapons manufacturer tests its 4 killer robots on heroin producers in the Golden Triangle in SEAsia. It goes haywire.

Title: 406. Don't Listen
description: Daniel and Sara have a 9-year-old son, Eric, and they've just moved to a new home not knowing the neighbours call it "the house of the voices". Eric is the first one to notice the odd noises behind each door.

Title: 407. Anything for Jackson
description: A bereaved Satanist couple kidnap a pregnant woman so they can use an ancient spellbook to put their dead grandson's spirit into her unborn child but end up summoning more than they bargained for.

Title: 408. No Mans Land
description: When Tommy goes on a road trip to meet Alice's family, things get out of hand and she gets kidnapped by a psychopath. Now, Tommy must journey into the unknown depths of bear county to rescue the love of his life. With time running out he has to adapt to his surroundings before its too late!

Title: 409. Mortal Kombat Legends: Scorpion's Revenge
description: Hanzo Hasashi loses his family during an attack by a rival clan the Lin Kuei. He is given the chance to compete in an inter-dimensional tournament to save his loved ones while other fighters try to save the Earth realm from annihilation.

Title: 410. Blue Ridge
description: A murder in a sleepy town at the heart of the Blue Ridge Mountains shocks the community and refuels a longtime feud between two families.

Title: 411. Quo Vadis, Aida?
description: Aida is a translator for the UN in the small town of Srebrenica. When the Serbian army takes over the town, her family is among the thousands of citizens looking for shelter in the UN camp.

Title: 412. Army of One
description: Out hiking, Special Forces Brenner Baker stumbles onto a cartel's compound. Her husband's killed and she's left for dead. The cartel made two mistakes - killing her husband and leaving her alive. They won't live to make another.

Title: 413. The Lovebirds
description: A couple (Issa Rae and Kumail Nanjiani) experiences a defining moment in their relationship when they are unintentionally embroiled in a murder mystery.

Title: 414. The Swing of Things
description: A groom-to-be accidentally books his destination wedding and honeymoon at a swingers resort in Jamaica.

Title: 415. Tanhaji: The Unsung Warrior
description: Tanhaji Malusare, a military chieftain in the army of the Maratha king Shivaji, leads the charge to capture the strategically important Kondhana fort guarded by the army of the fierce Rajput chieftain Udaybhan Rathod.

Title: 416. The Willoughbys
description: Convinced they'd be better off raising themselves, the Willoughby children hatch a sneaky plan to send their selfish parents on vacation. The siblings then embark on their own high-flying adventure to find the true meaning of family.

Title: 417. Horizon Line
description: A couple flying on a small plane to attend a tropical island wedding must fight for their lives after their pilot suffers a heart attack.

Title: 418. One Night in Miami...
description: A fictional account of one incredible night where icons Muhammad Ali, Malcolm X, Sam Cooke, and Jim Brown gathered discussing their roles in the Civil Rights Movement and cultural upheaval of the 60s.

Title: 419. Violet Evergarden: The Movie
description: After the aftermath of a war, a young girl who was used as a 'tool' for war learned to live. With the scars of burns, she goes back to her past to feel the true feelings of the Major's, "I love you."

Title: 420. Persian Lessons
description: A young Jewish man in a concentration camp has his life saved when executioners realize he owns a Persian book. Brought before a camp officer who wants to learn Farsi, Gilles agrees to teach him despite not knowing a word of the language.

Title: 421. Minamata
description: War photographer W. Eugene Smith travels back to Japan where he documents the devastating effect of mercury poisoning in coastal communities.

Title: 422. The Vanished
description: A husband and wife will stop at nothing to find their missing daughter, who disappeared on a family camping trip. When the police don't have any leads, the duo takes over.

Title: 423. Breach
description: On the cusp of fatherhood, a junior mechanic aboard an interstellar ark to New Earth must outwit a malevolent cosmic terror intent on using the spaceship as a weapon.

Title: 424. The Boys in the Band
description: At a birthday party in 1968 New York, a surprise guest and a drunken game leave seven gay friends reckoning with unspoken feelings and buried truths.

Title: 425. Saint-Narcisse
description: When a young man who thought his mother was dead discovers that she may still be alive, he goes on a quest to find her. His journey takes him to a remote cabin in the woods where his mother lives in exile with a mysterious young woman.

Title: 426. Nobody Sleeps in the Woods Tonight
description: A group of technology-dependent teenagers goes to offline camp and faces a deadly danger lurking in the woods.

Title: 427. Falling
description: John Peterson lives with his partner Eric and their adopted daughter in Southern California. When he is visited by his aging father who is searching for a place to retire, their two very different worlds collide.

Title: 428. Rose Island
description: An idealistic engineer builds his own island off the Italian coast and declares it a nation, drawing the world's attention. Values are tested when the Italian Government declares him an enemy, but to change the world risks must be taken.

Title: 429. Holly Slept Over
description: This unconventional comedy follows the relationship struggles of a married couple trying to conceive, their friends who have lost their spark, and the tension that ensues when an old college roommate stays over for the weekend.

Title: 430. Girl Lost: A Hollywood Story
description: Girl Lost: A Hollywood Story offers a glimpse into the lives of women involved in the sex industry through the interconnected stories of a teen runaway, single mother and two career escorts.

Title: 431. Meander
description: A woman finds herself locked in a series of strange tunnels full of deadly traps.

Title: 432. Debt Collectors
description: A pair of debt collectors are thrust into an explosively dangerous situation, chasing down various lowlifes while also evading a vengeful kingpin. -Samuel Goldwyn Films-

Title: 433. Rogue
description: O'Hara is a mercenary leading a squad of soldiers on their mission to rescue hostages in a remote part of Africa. Unfortunately, the mission goes awry and the team is stranded and forced to survive against the local rebels.

Title: 434. Love, Guaranteed
description: To save her small law firm, earnest lawyer Susan takes a high-paying case from Nick, a charming new client who wants to sue a dating website that guarantees love. But as the case heats up, so do Susan and Nick's feelings for each other.

Title: 435. Silver Skates
description: Matvey, the fastest courier on the frozen canals of 19th century St. Peteresburg is recruited by a group of pickpockets working the winter markets and falls for high-ranking official's daughter, Alisa.

Title: 436. The Book of Vision
description: Eva, a mysterious doctor, searches for an answer to her urgent dilemma as she unravels Dr. Anmuth's Book of Vision. Stellan gets involved in her life and is forced to confront his own nature as she faces the biggest decision of her life.

Title: 437. High Ground
description: In a bid to save the last of his family, Gutjuk, a young Aboriginal man, teams up with ex-soldier Travis to track down Baywara, the most dangerous warrior in the Territory, his uncle.

Title: 438. Sightless
description: After an attack renders her blind, Ellen Ashland withdraws from the world to recover. But soon she plunges into paranoia, unable to convince anyone that her assailant has returned to terrorize her by hiding in plain sight.

Title: 439. The Lost Husband
description: Trying to put her life back together after her husband's death, Libby and her children move to her estranged aunt's goat farm in central Texas.

Title: 440. Gabriel's Inferno: Part One
description: An intriguing exploration of seduction, forbidden love, and redemption, a captivating and passionate tale of one man's escape from his own personal hell as he tries to earn the impossible: forgiveness and love.

Title: 441. Disturbing the Peace
description: A small-town marshal who hasn't carried a gun since he left the Texas Rangers after a tragic shooting, must pick up his gun again to battle with a gang of outlaw bikers that has invaded the town to pull off a brazen and violent heist.

Title: 442. Deliver Us from Evil
description: Hit-man In-Nam kills Japanese mobster, enraging vengeful brother. Ex-lover Young-joo pleads for help but dies, her daughter missing. In-Nam must decide: flee to Panama or search for girl? Paths may cross with mobster brother.

Title: 443. No Escapes
description: A heroic story about firefighters and rescuers. What some may call an act of bravery is an ordinary day for them.

Title: 444. Rifkin's Festival
description: A married American couple goes to the San Sebastian Festival and gets caught up in the magic of the event, the beauty and charm of the city, and the fantasy of movies.

Title: 445. Occupation: Rainfall
description: Two years after aliens land on Earth, survivors from Sydney, Australia, fight in a desperate war as the number of casualties continue to grow.

Title: 446. Your Name Engraved Herein
description: In 1987, as martial law ends in Taiwan, Jia-han and Birdy fall in love amid family pressure, homophobia and social stigma.

Title: 447. Love Sarah
description: A young woman wishes to fulfill her mother's dream of opening her own bakery in Notting Hill, London. To do this, she enlists the help of an old friend and her grandma.

Title: 448. Initiation
description: Whiton University unravels the night a star-athlete is murdered, kicking off a spree of social media slayings that force students to uncover the truth behind the school's hidden secrets and the horrifying meaning of an exclamation point.

Title: 449. Dry Wind
description: A shy, middle-aged gay factory worker in the small town of Goiás, initiates casual sexual friendship with his co-worker Ricardo. But is later consumed with jealousy after a new arrival to town competes for Ricardo's attention.

Title: 450. Lazy Susan
description: A slice-of-life comedy about a woman on the edge with nowhere to go but over, Lazy Susan is a story about a spectacularly unmotivated woman for whom doing nothing is exhausting.

Title: 451. I'm Your Woman
description: In this 1970s set crime drama, a woman is forced to go on the run after her husband betrays his partners, sending her and her baby on a dangerous journey.

Title: 452. Really Love
description: Set in contemporary Washington D.C., a rising black painter strives to break into the competitive art world, while balancing a bittersweet romance he never expected.

Title: 453. The Christmas Chronicles: Part Two
description: Kate Pierce, now a cynical teen, is unexpectedly reunited with Santa Claus when a mysterious troublemaker threatens to cancel Christmas--forever.

Title: 454. Love Wedding Repeat
description: While trying to make his sister's wedding day go smoothly, Jack finds himself juggling an angry ex-girlfriend, an uninvited guest with a secret, a misplaced sleep sedative, and the girl who got away in alternate versions of the same day.

Title: 455. Taming the Younger Sister-in-Law
description: One day, Min-sang who is not that handsome becomes a huge success because of a webtoon. Then he gets a pretty wife, Yu-ra, for himself. Accidentally, he learns of his wife's dark past through his sister-in-law's diary.

Title: 456. Uncle Vanya
description: The Professor retires and moves back into his estate with his young wife, turning the lives of those who have been maintaining it in his absence upside down.

Title: 457. Shirley
description: A famous horror writer finds inspiration for her next book after she and her husband take in a young couple.

Title: 458. Post Mortem
description: A post mortem photographer and a little girl confront ghosts in a haunted village after the First World War.

Title: 459. Rogue City
description: Caught in the cross hairs of police corruption and Marseille's warring gangs, a loyal cop must protect his squad by taking matters into his own hands.

Title: 460. What Lies Below
description: A 16-year-old girl returns home from camp and learns that her mother has a new boyfriend, one she intends to marry. A man whose charm, intelligence and beauty make him look like he's not human at all.

Title: 461. Love, Weddings & Other Disasters
description: It is a multi-story romantic comedy about the people who work on weddings to create the perfect day for a loving couple - while their own relationships are outlandish, odd, crazy and far from perfect.

Title: 462. Beyto
description: Talented swimmer, motivated apprentice-- Beyto is in the midst of life, with a bright future ahead of him. But when the only son of a Turkish migrant family falls in love with his coach Mike, an ideal world falls to pieces.

Title: 463. The Stronghold
description: A police brigade working in the dangerous northern neighborhoods of Marseille, where the level of crime is higher than anywhere else in France.

Title: 464. Isi & Ossi
description: To realize their culinary and boxing dreams, the daughter of a billionaire forms a mutually beneficial alliance with the son of a struggling single mom.

Title: 465. Night in Paradise
description: Hiding out in Jeju Island following a brutal tragedy, a wronged mobster with a target on his back connects with a woman who has her own demons.

Title: 466. Run Sweetheart Run
description: After what seems to be an innocent date, Cherie now faces a night of terror when her date hunts her down and tries to kill her. She now must run for her life throughout the city and escape his grasp.

Title: 467. Stargirl
description: An unassuming high-schooler finds himself inexplicably drawn to the free-spirited new girl, whose unconventional ways change how they see themselves--and each other.

Title: 468. The Owners
description: A group of friends think they've found an easy score at an empty house with a safe full of cash, but when the elderly owners arrive home things begin to go awry.

Title: 469. Desperados
description: A panicked young woman, with her reluctant friends in tow, rushes to Mexico to try and delete a ranting email she sent to her new boyfriend.

Title: 470. The Block Island Sound
description: Something lurks off the coast of Block Island, silently influencing the behavior of fisherman, Tom Lynch. After suffering a series of violent outbursts, he unknowingly puts his family in grave danger.

Title: 471. After Love
description: Set in the port town of Dover, Mary Hussain suddenly finds herself a widow following the unexpected death of her husband. A day after the burial, she discovers he has a secret just twenty-one miles across the English Channel in Calais.

Title: 472. Trance
description: A disheartened motivational speaker gets hired by a corporate to become a preacher until his live stint on television puts him and his service under the scanner.

Title: 473. The Heist of the Century
description: In 2006, a group of thieves performed what is considered one of the most famous and smart bank heists in the history of Argentina when they rob the Banco Río branch in Acassuso.

Title: 474. Adam
description: A hard-living salesman becomes a quadriplegic after an accident.

Title: 475. Avalon
description: A long film compiled from sexual tapes recorded by the directors. It documents a six-year relationship in which mutual trust is being replaced little by little by isolation and distance.

Title: 476. Complete Strangers
description: A recovering alcoholic returns to his hometown after a hiatus and falls in love with a man who will turn his world upside down.

Title: 477. A Special Day
description: It's Josefin's birthday and all she wishes for is to be with her crush Niklas. But she doesn't know that Niklas have a crush on her as well and he is about to take the first step in their love story

Title: 478. Intelligent Design
description: When the paths of three scientists align, the fate of the robotics industry and the modern world is changed forever.

Title: 479. Last and First Men
description: Two billion years ahead of us, a future race of humans finds itself on the verge of extinction. Almost all that is left in the world are lone and surreal monuments, beaming their message into the wilderness.

Title: 480. Money Plane
description: A professional thief with $40 million in debt and his family's life on the line must commit one final heist - rob a futuristic airborne casino filled with the world's most dangerous criminals.

Title: 481. The Last Days of American Crime
description: In the not-too-distant future, as a final response to terrorism and crime, the U.S. government plans to broadcast a signal making it impossible for anyone to knowingly commit unlawful acts.

Title: 482. Beyond the Infinite Two Minutes
description: A cafe owner discovers that the TV in his cafe suddenly shows images from the future, but only two minutes into the future.

description: A fatal accident at a remote survivalist training camp sends participants into a panic - and sets the stage for a chilling showdown.

description: The Alterians face a cosmic threat from the Thanagarian Pleasure Pod, a mega-parasite that consumes their life essence, prompting Collector Maxy Prime and Gabby Minx to investigate.

description: The story of Ray-Ray McElrathbey, a freshman football player for Clemson University who secretly raised his younger brother on campus after his home life became too unsteady.

description: Sarah and Bob had very happy marriage,along there marriage life, Sarah was having affair with someone that her husband never knew.

Title: 491. Lost Bullet
description: A small time delinquent, turned police mechanic for a go fast task force, is forced to defend his innocence when his mentor is killed by dirty cops.

description: The police are on the trail of a serial killer, but with the victims being fellow officers, will they be able to catch the killer and solve the case in time?

description: For Luca it is the much-cited love at first sight: Sarah is not only loving and sexy, she gives him the kick that he has always dreamed of in his previous relationships. goes without saying things are going well, especially in bed.

Title: 497. Penguin Bloom
description: A family takes in an injured Magpie that makes a profound difference in their lives.

Title: 498. Scarlett
description: A college student must draw upon all the skills her spy-father taught her to protect herself and save her father from weapons dealers.

Title: 499. Shikara
description: Shikara is the story of resilience in the face of insurmountable odds. It's also the story of a love that remains unextinguished through 30 years of exile. A timeless love story in the worst of times.

Title: 500. HIT
description: An officer of the 'Homicide Intervention Team' who frequently suffers from having his panic attacks does everything in his power to rescue a woman who went missing.

Title: 501. The Quarry
description: A drifter (Shea Whigham) kills a traveling preacher and takes his place at a small-town church, but the police chief (Michael Shannon) suspects foul play.

Jan Lozano, Captain of the Fifth Brigade has fallen prisoner by an opponent's platoon along with a young driver while carrying out a mission that has been entrusted to him. The possibility of dying executed will soon be overtaken when a new unknown enemy arises. Both rival sides must unite and set their mutual hate aside in order to survive.

description: A troubled woman on the edge of divorce returns home to her younger sister after years apart. But when her sister and brother-in-law betray her trust, she embarks on a vicious crusade of revenge.

Title: 505. Welcome Home
description: A census report leads two female government teachers to an isolated house, in which resides a family with twisted secrets they never imagined to recover.

description: Deep in the ice of the antarctic, a team of geologists uncover an old Nazi laboratory still intact where dark experiments had occurred. In order to conquer the world, the Nazis created modified sharks who were able to fly.

description: When an all-powerful Superintelligence chooses to study average Carol Peters, the fate of the world hangs in the balance. As the A.I. decides to enslave, save or destroy humanity, it's up to Carol to prove that people are worth saving.

description: The film follows headstrong Ginny who meets Sunny for an arranged marriage, but turns him down, and then shows how Sunny teams up with Ginny's mother to win her love.

description: Angèle and Adam form a young ideal couple. A few years pass. One evening, they meet again. Strangers to each other, can their love come back to life ?

description: In the near future, a financial crisis will hit Korea and slums arise. From those areas, a group of young people commit crime to survive.

description: Dong-gook, who is thinking of remarrying, introduces his stepmother Kyeong-sook to his son Jin-yeong. At the family gathering, Jin-yeong is surprised to see his stepmother's younger brother Hyeon-sook who was his one-night stand recently.

description: Cristina, a journalist of Mexican origin, travels to her ancestral home in Veracruz to investigate a story of sorcery and healing. There, she is kidnapped by a group of locals who claim she's the devil incarnated.

description: With the fall of the alien ship Julia's life changed, now three years later mankind is about to experience new encounter.

description: The true story of one young white Southerner in the Summer of 1961, caught in a place and time where he had to choose which side he was on.

description: Dublin teenagers Matthew, nihilistic Rez, and the deranged Kearney, leave school to a social vacuum of drinking and drugs, falling into shocking acts of transgression.

description: In seaside Italy, a Holocaust survivor with a daycare business takes in a 12-year-old street kid who recently robbed her.

description: What began as a friendship turns into a fierce romance in this heart-wrenching drama. LUZ is a story of survival, not only for the lives of both men, but for their relationship as it transitions to the world outside their cell.

description: A university professor's ignorance is exposed when he must prepare a student for a debate.

Title: 533. Castle Freak
description: An Albanian castle with bloodthirsty creatures is inherited by a young blind woman.

Title: 534. The Bones on Greenwich Shore
description: A Japanese woman falls for an older British painter, then faces the possibility they could be related.

description: Ellie tries to mend her marriage with her husband Marcus after a brief encounter with an old friend, David, only to find that David is more dangerous and unstable than she'd realized.

description: A disgraced doctor and his family are held hostage at their home by criminals on the run, when a robbery-gone-awry requires them to seek immediate medical attention.

description: A tale of family, friendships and betrayal in the violent world of the Philadelphia mob.

description: After a prank blows up on a high school senior's life, he shares a list of certain things he wishes he'd done differently.

description: A documentary that focuses on a dangerously legendary water park and its slew of injuries and crimes along with child safety concerns.

description: A vacationing couple must discover the mystery behind a strange video that shows one of them killing the other.

description: After discovering a magical mask, an 11-year-old aspiring wrestler enters a competition to become the next WWE superstar.

description: Set in a time where all drugs and alcohol are illegal, the only day anyone can participate in the "fun" is on Binge day.

description: Based on the story of renowned butterfly expert Robert Pyle (David Cross) who embarked on a life-changing trek through one of America's most important unprotected wildlands in the summer of 1995.

description: When a young woman meets an aspiring saxophonist in her father's record shop in 1950s Harlem, their love ignites a sweeping romance that transcends changing times, geography, and professional success.

description: Suspecting his wife of infidelity, Jerry follows his friend down a dark rabbit hole into a horror landscape of addiction.

description: After meeting online, lovers Aviva and Eden navigate a turbulent relationship, marriage, separation, and reconciliation efforts amid internal and external conflicts stemming from their complex personalities.

description: A young police officer, Cristi, tries to find the balance between two opposing parts of his identity: that of a man working in a macho hierarchical environment and that of a closeted gay person who tries to keep his personal life a secret.

Title: 556. Hard Kill
description: The work of billionaire tech CEO Donovan Chalmers (Willis) is so valuable that he hires mercenaries to protect it, and a terrorist group kidnaps his daughter just to get it.

description: A successful architect is approached on his trip to the Paris Airport by a chatty girl. Although the meeting seems fortuitous, soon there be a turn that will transform the encounter into something much more sinister and criminal.

description: Maria, Pinuccia, Lia, Katia and Antonella are five sisters who live in an apartment in Palermo. When Antonella accidentally dies, the sisters' relationships are turned upside down for the rest of their lives.

description: A group of young friends from the Bronx fight to save their neighborhood from gentrification...and vampires.

description: His own body turned into a living work of art and promptly exhibited in a museum, Sam, a Syrian refugee, will soon realize to have sold away more than just his skin.

description: About a software Techie(Janani) and A Brutal Rapist gang who tried to Assassinate Janani And later how Janani escaped from that gang with her intelligence by throwing the strongest and emotional weapon called Love.

description: Katsuragi is a disillusioned office worker who drunkenly attempts to commit suicide. However, with the help of a mysterious saviour, he soon discovers there are fates even worse than death.

description: An alien takes control of a drug-addicted man's body, leading to debauchery and chaos as the visitor explores humanity through Cape Town's underworld of drugs, sex, and violence.

Title: 565. Bulbbul
description: A man returns home after years to find his brother's child bride now grown up and abandoned, and his ancestral village plagued by mysterious deaths.

Title: 566. Dragon Rider
description: A young silver dragon teams up with a mountain spirit and an orphaned boy on a journey through the Himalayas in search for the Rim of Heaven.

description: To avenge her mother's death, Pixie masterminds a heist but must flee across Ireland from gangsters, take on the patriarchy, and choose her own destiny.

description: Five friends exploring a remote cave system in Northern Australia find themselves threatened by a hungry crocodile.

Title: 569. Fireball: Visitors from Darker Worlds
description: A documentary from Werner Herzog about meteors and comets and their influence on ancient religions and other cultural and physical impacts they've had on Earth.

description: It is the story of the all-black Twenty-Fourth United States Infantry Regiment, and the Houston Riot of 1917.

description: Set over 24 hours in London, a man goes on a bold and reckless journey of self-liberation.

description: Twelve-year-old Kareem Manning hires a criminal to scare his mom's new boyfriend -police officer James Coffee - but it backfires, forcing Coffee and Kareem to team up in order to save themselves from Detroit's most ruthless drug kingpin.

description: When you think marrying your best friend means a 'happily ever-after', but it turns out to be just the reverse.

description: Two thieving teenage brothers, stealing money to help their sick mom, match wits with a troubled security guard stuck at the bottom of a forgotten well.

description: A ruthless businesswoman is abducting young women as part of a gruesome bio-hacking experiment to reverse the aging process. When Mia goes to investigate, she finds herself trapped, branded and tortured in an underground medical facility.

Title: 577. The Show
description: A man's search for a stolen artifact leads him to the haunted town filled with Voodoo gangsters, masked adventurers, Depression-era private eyes and violent chiaroscuro women.

description: Following the launch of her new novel, 35-year-old writer Kate's former professor invites her to speak at her alma mater. After accepting the invitation, Kate finds herself deeply enmeshed in the lives of a group of college students.

description: After Sang-Won's daughter Yi-Na goes missing in their new home, a mysterious man approaches him and tells him to look for her in the closet.

description: When a possessed pair of jeans begins to kill the staff of a trendy clothing store, it is up to Libby, an idealistic young salesclerk, to stop its bloody rampage.

Title: 583. Uncle Peckerhead
description: When a punk band scores their first tour, life on the road proves tough when they are joined by a man-eating demon as a roadie.

description: The famed stepbrother inventors know what they're gonna do today. They're gonna rescue their sister from an alien abduction.

description: When Harvard hockey's Bobby Sanders lands in Sweden's minor leagues, his relationship with the girl at the local market forces him to confront the reality of his childhood NHL dream before the Hockey Gods intervene.

description: A reboot of the famous Swedish saga "Jönssonligan" ("The Jönsson Gang")

Title: 589. M.O.M. Mothers of Monsters
description: A distraught mother suspects her teenage son of plotting a school shooting, but when the system ignores her, she's forced to take matters into her own hands.

Title: 590. Fate/Grand Order the Movie: Divine Realm of the Round Table: Camelot
description: Chaldea agents Ritsuka Fujimaru and Mash Kyrielight travel to Camelot and encounter the heroes of that realm.

Title: 591. Under the Riccione Sun
description: On holiday at Riccione beach, a group of teens get to know each other and help each other get through summer loves' heartache.

description: A group of thieves are sent out to hunt for urban legends by a wealthy man intending to open a museum full of mythical creatures. Soon, the thieves learn first-hand the legend of the Leprechaun.

description: The story revolves around two siblings and their struggle to find solid ground in the homes of their alcoholic father and negligent mother. The children ultimately run away and find a temporary life for themselves.

Title: 596. 10 Things We Should Do Before We Break Up
description: After Abigail, a single mom of two, becomes pregnant following a one-night stand with Ben, the unlikely pair try to make a go of it.

Title: 597. Ludo
description: From a resurfaced sex tape to a rogue suitcase of money, four wildly different stories overlap at the whims of fate, chance and one eccentric criminal.

Title: 598. Death Files
description: 2 locksmiths find a flash drive at an old warehouse. One of them activates the flash drive at a computer and opens the shocking world of mysterious creatures, broken lives and violence.

Title: 599. All My Friends Are Dead
description: During the New Year's Eve party of a bunch of friends, a series of crazy events brings out secrets, breaks hearts and leads to a shocking ending.

Title: 600. My Heart Can't Beat Unless You Tell It To
description: Two mysterious siblings find themselves at odds over care for their frail and sickly younger brother.
